  "prompt": "Why do I see the same questions in my Quora feed even if I refresh?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why you're seeing repetitive questions on Quora:\n\n1. Limited content: Depending on your interests and followed topics, there might be a limited pool of new questions.\n\n2. Algorithm issues: Quora's recommendation algorithm might be temporarily glitching or not refreshing properly.\n\n3. Cache problems: Your browser or app might be caching old content.\n\n4. Low activity in your followed topics: Some niche subjects have less frequent new content.\n\n5. Technical glitch: There could be a temporary issue with Quora's content delivery system.\n\nTo resolve this, you can try:\n- Clearing your browser cache\n- Logging out and logging back in\n- Updating the Quora app\n- Following more topics or writers\n- Manually adjusting your topic preferences\n\nIf the issue persists, you might want to contact Quora support directly.",
